title: LIVE: Zamalek v Ahly (Egypt Super Cup) - Egyptian Football - Sports
text:
14:00 The Cairo derby game will take place in the Hazza Bin Zayed Stadium in Al-Ain city. The venue hosts up to 25,000 supporters.
13:30 Zamalek's starting lineup: Ahmed El-Shenawy; Ahmed Tawfik, Ali Gabr, Ahmed Dwidar, Hamada Tolba; Maarouf Youssef, Tarek Hamed, Omar Gaber; Mahmoud Kahraba, Mohamed Ibrahim, Bassem Morsi
13:00 It's the second time for Ahly and Zamalek to clash away from home in a competitive match in their long history as the first meeting was more than 20 years ago in the African Super Cup in Johannesburg in 1994.
12:30 Ahly's icon Abdel-Aziz Abdel-Shafy 'Zizo' was named as a stop-gap boss to lead Ahly in the Super Cup after the dismissal of coach Fathi Mabrouk
12:00 Argentina icon Diego Armando Maradona, who was coaching UAE side Al-Wasl, will attend the Egypt Super Cup game between Zamalek and Ahly.
11:30 Ahly, hit by unfamiliar internal wrangling and board disputes, are desperate to give their fans something to cheer about after finishing last season without winning a major trophy for the first time since 2004, with bitter foes Zamalek claiming the domestic double.
11:00 Zamalek will be eager to win the treble when face Ahly in Thursday's Egypt's Super Cup in the United Arab Emirates in a rare match overseas as the new season gets underway.
Stay tuned as the match is due to start at 18:00 Cairo time (GMT+2)
Venue: Hazza Bin Zayed Stadium (United Arab Emirates)
Referee: Carlos Velasco Carballo (Spain)
